# Environment

- **OS:** Windows. The integrated shell is **bash** (Git Bash), so prefer
 POSIX-style commands and forward slashes in shell snippets.
- **Node version manager:** **fnm** (`1.39.x`). The repo should pin a Node
 version via `.node-version` (fnm reads it automatically). Don't assume `nvm`.
- **Node:** `v24.x` (currently `24.17.0`). **npm:** `11.x` (currently `11.13.0`).
- **Package manager:** **npm** (not pnpm/yarn) unless the user says otherwise.
- **git:** `2.54.x`.

## Repos in this workspace

- `Findias` — the Electron + TypeScript + React (MUI, Vite via electron-vite,
 Vitest) **mod manager**. Built/distributed via GitHub Releases on
 `tekashi-side/Findias`; self-updates via electron-updater.
- `Uiscias` — the **mods** source (`.it` files), published as GitHub releases on
 `Root50199/Uiscias`. Findias's source of truth for available mods.

## Conventions

- All app code is **TypeScript** where possible; main/preload/renderer share types.
- See `docs/architecture.md` for the technical design and `docs/project-overview.md`
 / `docs/game-structure.md` for product/domain context.

## Gotcha (agent-only): Windows drive-letter casing breaks Vitest

This affects the **AI agent's automated tool shell**, not the user. The user's
own bash (`cd /c/code/Findias`) and PowerShell shells canonicalize to uppercase
`C:` and run everything (`npm run dev`, `npm test`) without issue.

The agent's tool shell sometimes starts with a **lowercase** drive cwd
(`c:\code\Findias`). With a lowercase `c:`, Vitest loads two copies of
`@vitest/runner` and every test fails during collection with
`TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'config')`.

Agent fix: prefix commands so the cwd canonicalizes to uppercase via the Git Bash
`/c/` mount:

```bash
cd /c/code/Findias && npm test
```

`process.cwd()` should print `C:\code\Findias` (uppercase `C`). Typecheck/build
are unaffected.
